@startuml Component Interaction Diagram
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title AI-Based Code Reviewer - Component Interaction Diagram\nPull Request Review Flow

actor "Developer" as dev
participant "GitHub" as github
participant "Webhook\nHandler" as webhook
participant "Redis\nQueue" as redis
participant "Code Review\nEngine" as review
participant "AST\nParser" as parser
participant "Architecture\nAnalyzer" as arch
participant "Neo4j\nDatabase" as neo4j
participant "Agentic AI\nService" as ai
participant "LLM API\n(GPT-4/Claude)" as llm
participant "PostgreSQL\nDatabase" as postgres
participant "Notification\nService" as notify

== Pull Request Creation ==
dev -> github: Create/Update PR
activate github
github -> webhook: POST /api/webhooks/github\n(PR event payload)
activate webhook
webhook -> webhook: Verify webhook signature
webhook -> redis: Queue analysis task
activate redis
redis --> webhook: Task queued
deactivate redis
webhook --> github: 200 OK
deactivate webhook
github --> dev: PR created
deactivate github

== Analysis Processing ==
redis -> review: Dequeue analysis task
activate review
review -> github: GET /repos/{owner}/{repo}/pulls/{pr_number}
activate github
github --> review: PR details
deactivate github

review -> github: GET /repos/{owner}/{repo}/pulls/{pr_number}/files
activate github
github --> review: Changed files diff
deactivate github

== Code Parsing ==
review -> parser: parse_files(changed_files)
activate parser
parser -> parser: Generate AST for each file
parser -> parser: Extract entities\n(classes, functions, imports)
parser -> parser: Extract dependencies
parser --> review: AST + entities + dependencies
deactivate parser

== Architecture Context ==
review -> arch: get_architectural_context(project_id)
activate arch
arch -> neo4j: MATCH (m:Module {project_id: $id})\nRETURN m, dependencies
activate neo4j
neo4j --> arch: Existing dependency graph
deactivate neo4j
arch -> arch: Analyze architectural patterns
arch -> arch: Identify potential violations
arch --> review: Architectural context + patterns
deactivate arch

== AI Analysis ==
review -> ai: analyze_code(code, context, rules)
activate ai
ai -> ai: Build LLM prompt\n(code + context + compliance rules)
ai -> llm: POST /v1/chat/completions\n(analysis request)
activate llm
llm -> llm: Analyze code quality\nDetect issues\nGenerate suggestions
llm --> ai: Analysis response
deactivate llm

alt LLM API Failure
    ai -> llm: Retry with secondary LLM (Claude)
    activate llm
    llm --> ai: Fallback response
    deactivate llm
end

ai -> ai: Parse LLM response
ai -> ai: Extract issues and suggestions
ai -> ai: Categorize by severity
ai --> review: Structured analysis results
deactivate ai

== Store Results ==
review -> postgres: INSERT INTO analyses\n(pr_id, status, issues)
activate postgres
postgres --> review: Analysis ID
deactivate postgres

review -> postgres: INSERT INTO issues\n(analysis_id, severity, description)
activate postgres
postgres --> review: Issue IDs
deactivate postgres

== Update Dependency Graph ==
review -> arch: update_dependency_graph(entities, dependencies)
activate arch
arch -> neo4j: CREATE/MERGE nodes and relationships
activate neo4j
neo4j --> arch: Graph updated
deactivate neo4j

arch -> neo4j: MATCH circular dependencies
activate neo4j
neo4j --> arch: Circular dependency list
deactivate neo4j
arch --> review: Graph update complete
deactivate arch

== Post Review Comments ==
review -> github: POST /repos/{owner}/{repo}/pulls/{pr_number}/comments
activate github
github --> review: Comments posted
deactivate github

== Send Notifications ==
review -> notify: send_notification(pr_author, analysis_results)
activate notify
notify -> notify: Format notification
notify --> dev: Email/Slack notification
deactivate notify

review -> redis: Mark task as completed
activate redis
redis --> review: Task status updated
deactivate redis
deactivate review

== Developer Reviews Feedback ==
dev -> github: View PR comments
activate github
github --> dev: Display analysis results
deactivate github

dev -> github: Accept/Dismiss issues
activate github
github -> webhook: Webhook: issue_comment
activate webhook
webhook -> postgres: UPDATE issues\nSET user_feedback = 'accept'
activate postgres
postgres --> webhook: Feedback recorded
deactivate postgres
webhook --> github: 200 OK
deactivate webhook
deactivate github

note over dev, postgres
  Total processing time: 8-12 seconds for <10K LOC
  - Webhook processing: <1s
  - Code parsing: 2-3s
  - LLM analysis: 3-5s
  - Graph update: 1-2s
  - Comment posting: 1-2s
end note

@enduml
